{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-template-excerpt-js","path":"/excerpts/nature_chasing_sunlight_poem/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>Ever too soon the sunlight goes,<br>\nWhile up in the sky Virgo shows,<br>\nHarsh false light will be all we'll know,<br>\nAs the march of autumn shan't slow,<br>\nTiring so as to relax,<br>\nA perfect picture soon shows cracks,<br>\nSo few sand grains till blue turns black,<br>\nThen an age till the sky's won back,<br>\nAs the year becomes short of days,<br>\nEvenings are lit by a brief haze,<br>\nThere's but so few days that aren't grey,<br>\nWe're to enjoy those that we may,<br>\nLush grass and sunshine as a muse,<br>\nIt's something that's so sad to lose,<br>\nFor from such beauty one takes cue,<br>\nOnce gone you know its true value.</p>","frontmatter":{"date":"January 06, 2020","title":"Chasing Sunlight","audio":{"publicURL":"/static/a485bfe49b65b233f553e3c6356a1257/Christian Lacdael - Nature - 06 Chasing Sunlight.mp3"},"icon":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/jpeg;base64,","aspectRatio":1,"src":"/static/dbe3d7eed1aa21bc6cd7c807bf23bd82/7d509/poem_on_nature_chasing_sunlight.jpg","srcSet":"/static/dbe3d7eed1aa21bc6cd7c807bf23bd82/f836f/poem_on_nature_chasing_sunlight.jpg 200w,\n/static/dbe3d7eed1aa21bc6cd7c807bf23bd82/2244e/poem_on_nature_chasing_sunlight.jpg 400w,\n/static/dbe3d7eed1aa21bc6cd7c807bf23bd82/7d509/poem_on_nature_chasing_sunlight.jpg 720w","sizes":"(max-width: 720px) 100vw, 720px"}}}}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/excerpts/nature_chasing_sunlight_poem/"}},"staticQueryHashes":["3649515864"]}